Executives Attack U.K. Government on Aviation Policy, Times Says

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-03-30T00:29:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/executives-attack-u-k-government-on-aviation-policy-times-says.html
Seventy-four senior executives
accuse the U.K. government of failing to establish an aviation
policy to spur the growth of the economy, the London-based Times
reported, citing a letter to the newspaper from the executives.
The letter describes U.K. airports as being overstretched,
congested and prone to disruption, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
